{{italic title}} The {{Nihongo|'''''Japanese Pharmacopoeia'''''|日本薬局方|}} is the official [[pharmacopoeia]] of [[Japan]]. It is published by the {{Nihongo|[[Pharmaceuticals and Medical Devices Agency]]|独立行政法人 医薬品医療機器総合機構|}} under the authority of the [[Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare]].<ref>{{cite web|title=業務のご案内 2012-2013 |url=http://www.pmda.go.jp/guide/file/profile_of_services2012-2013.pdf |publisher=Pharmaceuticals and Medical Devices Agency |accessdate=11 September 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121029031534/http://www.pmda.go.jp/guide/file/profile_of_services2012-2013.pdf |archivedate=29 October 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=History＆Legal Status |url=http://www.pmda.go.jp/english/pharmacopoeia/pdf/jpdata/History&Law_20110701.pdf |accessdate=11 September 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131228060405/http://www.pmda.go.jp/english/pharmacopoeia/pdf/jpdata/History%26Law_20110701.pdf |archivedate=28 December 2013 |df= }}</ref> The first edition was published on 25 June, 1886, with revisions being issued from time to time. The current revision is number 17, issued electronically in English language on 7 March 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=Japanese Pharmacopoeia 17|url=https://www.pmda.go.jp/english/rs-sb-std/standards-development/jp/0019.html|work=Japanese Pharmacopoeia 17|accessdate=17 November 2016}}</ref>
