'''Jesse Sheidlower''' (born August 5, 1968)<ref>[http://staugustine.com/stories/092004/opi_2587842.shtml St. Augustine's.com]</ref> is an [[author]] and [[copy editing|editor]] specializing in [[English language|English]] and [[lexicography]].  From 1999 until 2005 he was Principal North American Editor at the [[Oxford English Dictionary]]; then he was editor-at-large focusing on North American usage.<ref>[http://public.oed.com/the-oed-today/staff-of-the-oxford-english-dictionary/former-staff-of-the-oed/ OED Former Staff Page]</ref> He left the OED in 2013.

==Biography==
Sheidlower received an undergraduate degree in English from the [[University of Chicago]].<ref>[http://magazine.uchicago.edu/0102/features/search.html University of Chicago Magazine article]</ref>

Although not a computer programmer by training, Sheidlower introduced [[Perl]] to the North American offices of Oxford University Press and developed tools for data manipulation when no programmers were available.<ref>[http://www.oreilly.com/pub/a/oreilly/perl/news/oxford_0900.html Perl Enters The Oxford English Dictionary]</ref>  He is also one of the core developers of [https://metacpan.org/module/Catalyst Catalyst], a popular Perl web development framework.

