{{Infobox dot-com company | name = MetroLyrics | logo = MetroLyrics logo.svg | foundation = {{start date and age|2002|12|30}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://whois.domaintools.com/metrolyrics.com|title=MetroLyrics.com WHOIS, DNS, & Domain Info - DomainTools|work=[[WHOIS]]|date= |accessdate=2016-03-26}}</ref> | founder = [[Milun Tesovic]], Alan Juristovski | location_city = [[Vancouver]], British Columbia | location_country = Canada | services = [[Lyrics]] | parent = [[CBS Interactive]] | homepage = [http://www.metrolyrics.com/ MetroLyrics.com] | num_employees = 10+<ref>[https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/music/metrolyrics-how-a-bc-teen-created-one-of-the-worlds-biggest-music-sites/article566735/ MetroLyrics: How a B.C. teen created one of the world's biggest music sites]</ref> |alexa={{Decrease}} 4,550 ({{as of|2018|10|18|alt=October 2018}})<ref name="alexa">{{cite web|url=http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/metrolyrics.com|title=MetroLyrics.com Site Info|publisher=[[Alexa Internet]]|accessdate= 2018-04-02}}</ref> }} '''MetroLyrics''' is a [[lyrics]]-dedicated website, founded in December 2002. The MetroLyrics database contains over 1 million songs performed by over 16,000 artists.
==History== MetroLyrics was the first lyrics-dedicated site to license licensing aggregator [[Gracenote]] Inc.'s lyrics catalogue in April 2008.<ref>[http://metroleap.com/releases.php Metroleap.com] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110226195814/http://metroleap.com/releases.php |date=2011-02-26 }}</ref> Through this lyrics licensing model, lyrics copyright holders accrue royalty revenue when their work is displayed on MetroLyrics.com, which MetroLyrics recuperates by collecting money from [[banner advertisement]]s on the site. Royalties are paid on all displayed lyrics and are handled through Gracenote. In January 2013, [[LyricFind]] acquired Gracenote's lyrics licensing business, merging it in with their own.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lyricfind.com/gracenote-larry-marcus/ |title=Welcoming Gracenote and Larry Marcus! |date=January 15, 2013 |accessdate=March 14, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141109054655/http://www.lyricfind.com/gracenote-larry-marcus/ |archivedate=November 9, 2014 |df= }}</ref> MetroLyrics' licensing model is distinct, as many lyrics websites still offer content that is allegedly unlicensed and [[Copyright infringement|copyright infringing]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Plambeck|first=Joseph|title=Lyrics Sites at Center of Fight Over Royalties|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=May 9, 2010|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/05/10/business/media/10lyrics.html?_r=1&scp=1&sq=lyrics%20royalty&st=cse|accessdate=May 9, 2010}}</ref>
MetroLyrics was acquired by [[CBS Interactive]] in October 2011.<ref>{{cite web| title = CBS Interactive Music Group broadens distribution of its core assets to metrolyrics.com's Global Audience of more than 25 million users| url = http://www.cbsradio.com/press_center/releases/pressrelease100819-10-06-2011.html| accessdate = October 6, 2011| deadurl = yes| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20111008111342/http://www.cbsradio.com/press_center/releases/pressrelease100819-10-06-2011.html| archivedate = October 8, 2011| df = }}</ref>
